    "notes": "Soprano recorder in C is the standard elementary school instrument. Non-transposing (concert pitch, treble clef). English (Baroque) fingering is the professional standard and most common system worldwide. German fingering differs only for F and Bb — it simplifies those notes but makes F# and Bb harder. WFG covers both; our data uses English. The same fingerings apply to all C recorders (soprano, tenor, great bass). For F recorders (sopranino, alto, bass), the same fingering patterns apply but the note names are transposed up a 4th."
  },
